summary: Email from Southwest Airlines subpoena specialist Ren Nathan to an unspecified recipient, transmitting documents responsive to a grand jury subpoena. The email states Southwest produced documents from its CIRRUS database but was unable to locate records for Ghislaine Maxwell and notes a 10-year records retention policy limiting availability to post-January 28, 2010.

persons.name: Ren Nathan
persons.role: Subpoena Research Specialist, General Counsel - Litigation at Southwest Airlines

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Identified as a person for whom Southwest Airlines was unable to locate responsive travel records; also referenced by the alias Ghislaine Borgerson.

events.title: Southwest Airlines responds to grand jury subpoena
events.description: Ren Nathan of Southwest Airlines transmits documents from its CIRRUS database responsive to a grand jury subpoena, noting no records found for Ghislaine Maxwell and citing a 10-year records retention limit.

locations: 2702 Love Field Drive HDG-4GC Dallas, TX 75235
keyFacts: Southwest Airlines produced documents from its CIRRUS database in response to a grand jury subpoena, bates numbered SWA000001 to SWA000008.
Southwest Airlines was unable to locate any responsive travel records for Ghislaine Maxwell (also known as Ghislaine Borgerson).
Southwest Airlines' records retention policy for travel records only goes back 10 years, so no records prior to January 28, 2010, would be available.
The communication is dated January 29, 2020, indicating ongoing grand jury investigative activity related to Ghislaine Maxwell at that time.
The email includes a confidentiality notice, treating the subpoena response as legally privileged information.
